text: Enonkoski is a municipality in Southern Savonia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 1,321 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Heinävesi, Savonlinna and Varkaus. It has a church in the centre, built in 1886. Enonkoski was founded in 1882. == Villages == Hanhijärvi, Ihamaniemi, Joutsenmäki, Karvila, Laasala, Makkola, Muhola, Paakkunala, Parkumäki, Simanala, Suurimäki and Vuorikoski == Other websites == * Municipality of Enonkoski – Official website Category:1882 establishments in Europe Category:1880s establishments in Finland Category:Municipalities of South Savo
